[[爛蕃茄|爛蕃茄]]上收集的270篇專業影評文章中，有232篇給予該片「新鮮」的正面評價，「新鮮度」為86%，平均得分7.6分（滿分10分），該網站的共識性評價寫道「就如同科技人才共同創立出的科技巨頭一般，《史帝夫賈伯斯》匯集了卓越的演員，提供了一部優雅下潛藏著複雜的電影」<ref name=RT>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/steve_jobs_2015/ |title=Steve Jobs (2015) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=2016-09-07 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.rottentomatoes.com%2Fm%2Fsteve_jobs_2015%2F&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而基於另一影評匯總網站[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]上的45篇評論文章，其中41篇予以好評，1篇差評，3篇褒貶不一，平均分為82（滿分100），綜合結果為「普遍良好的評價」<ref name=met>{{cite web |title=Steve Jobs reviews |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/steve-jobs |publisher=Metacritic |accessdate=2015-11-09 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.metacritic.com%2Fmovie%2Fsteve-jobs&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。據[[影院評分|CinemaScore]]進行的調查，觀眾的平均評價於A+至F間落於「A-」<ref name="opening"/>。

《[[好萊塢報導|好萊塢報導]]》的[[陶德·麥卡錫|陶德·麥卡錫]]表示，鮑伊「激勵人心」的導演功力「優雅的輔助了索金在三幕中極具戲劇性的探討」，並稱讚法斯賓達的演出，「儘管他的身材並不像該角色的本尊，[但]他完全可以教會我們如何來看待這個人的本質」<ref name=hrrev>{{cite web |last=McCarthy |first=Todd |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movie/steve-jobs/review/820561 |title='Steve Jobs': Telluride Review |accessdate=2015-09-06 |date=2015-09-06 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hollywoodreporter.com%2Fmovie%2Fsteve-jobs%2Freview%2F820561&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[綜藝_(雜誌)|綜藝]]》雜誌的賈斯汀·張稱該片為「狂亂且富創意的狂想曲」以及「一部卓越、瘋狂、含巧妙設計及怪異自誇的電影」<ref name="variety">{{cite news |title=Telluride Film Review: ''Steve Jobs'' |url=http://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/steve-jobs-review-michael-fassbender-telluride-film-festival-1201586996/ |last=Chang |first=Justin |date=2015-09-06 |accessdate=2015-09-06 |work=Variety |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2015%2Ffilm%2Ffestivals%2Fsteve-jobs-review-michael-fassbender-telluride-film-festival-1201586996%2F&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[Salon.com|Salon.com]]》的安德魯·奧黑爾認為電影的結構合情合理，不僅稱讚電影的劇本是「索金有史以來最令人滿意的劇本」，同時也對電影讚譽有加，稱《史帝夫賈伯斯》「是鮑伊的導演生涯中最為優秀的電影作品」<ref>{{cite web | last = O'Hehir | first = Andrew | title = Steve Jobs: Michael Fassbender stars in a riveting three-act moral drama — that has nothing to do with computers | work = [[Salon.com|Salon.com]] | url = http://www.salon.com/2015/10/07/steve_jobs_michael_fassbender_stars_in_a_riveting_three_act_moral_drama_that_has_nothing_to_do_with_computers/ | date = 2015-10-08 | accessdate = 2017-05-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170114052726/http://www.salon.com/2015/10/07/steve_jobs_michael_fassbender_stars_in_a_riveting_three_act_moral_drama_that_has_nothing_to_do_with_computers/ | archive-date = 2017-01-14 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》的{{link-en|A·O·史考特|A. O. Scott}}稱該片為一部「大膽、腦力激盪的娛樂電影」，並認為《史帝夫賈伯斯》對「好萊塢電影一貫的懶惰劇情」及「當代大螢幕評論家眼中盛宴的定義」來說是一大挑戰<ref>{{cite web |last=Scott |first=A. O. |title=Review: Steve Jobs, Apple’s Visionary C.E.O. Dissected |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/09/movies/review-steve-jobs-apples-visionary-ceo-dissected.html?partner=rss&emc=rss |date=2015-10-09 |accessdate=2017-05-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529084050/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/09/movies/review-steve-jobs-apples-visionary-ceo-dissected.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&_r=2 |archive-date=2017-05-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[衛報|衛報]]》的班傑明·李給予電影3顆星（滿分5星）的評價，寫道「儘管電影不停的告訴你，一切事物都是那麼的重要，但令人失望的是，真正關心當下發生的事是如此難的事情」。他指責索金「主導」劇本的行為，認為「對白令人窒息」，且「片中演員試圖扼殺足夠的呼吸空間來呈現自己的東西」<ref name=guarrev>{{cite web |last=Lee |first=Benjamin |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/sep/06/steve-jobs-movie-review-michael-fassbender-telluride |title=Steve Jobs review: Fassbender excels but iWorship required if you're to care |accessdate=2015-09-12 |date=2015-09-06 |work=The Guardian |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ffilm%2F2015%2Fsep%2F06%2Fsteve-jobs-movie-review-michael-fassbender-telluride&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《紐約時報》的{{link-en|喬·諾科拉|Joe Nocera}}對賈伯斯十分了解，質疑「電影與賈伯斯本尊之間有多少的關聯性」。他認為該片純屬「虛構」，並繼續說，「索金和飾演賈伯斯的演員麥可·法斯賓達都未能在任何定義上捕捉到他的身影」<ref name=Nocera>{{cite news |last1=Nocera |first1=Joe |title=Aaron Sorkin's ''Steve Jobs'' Con |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/13/opinion/aaron-sorkins-steve-jobs-con.html |accessdate=2015-10-14 |work=The New York Times |date=2015-10-13 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2015%2F10%2F13%2Fopinion%2Faaron-sorkins-steve-jobs-con.html&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 票房 ===

《史帝夫賈伯斯》在北美的票房收入為1,780萬美元，其他地區1,670萬美元，全球總計3,440萬美元<ref name=BOM />。

在有限上映的首個週末，該片在四家劇院中收穫了521,000美元的票房，平均每家劇院的收入約為130,250美元，擊敗了《[[怒火邊界|怒火邊界]]》（67,000美元）成為2015年最佳的劇院平均收入<ref name="Limited">{{cite web |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |url=http://deadline.com/2015/10/martian-pan-the-walk-weekend-box-office-1201572119/ |title='Martian' Still Has Fuel In Its Second Frame; 'Pan' Walks Plank; 'Steve Jobs' Popular In NY & LA – Monday Postmortem |publisher=[[Deadline.com|Deadline.com]] |date=2015-10-12 |accessdate=2015-11-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdeadline.com%2F2015%2F10%2Fmartian-pan-the-walk-weekend-box-office-1201572119%2F&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。電影於10月23日正式廣泛發行，與同期上映的《[[獵巫行動：大滅絕|獵巫行動：大滅絕]]》、《{{link-en|鬼入鏡5：鬼次元|Paranormal Activity: The Ghost Dimension}}》、《{{link-en|沙漠飆高音|Rock the Kasbah (film)}}》和《{{link-en|芙蓉仙子|Jem and the Holograms (film)}}》共同競爭。外界原先預測《史帝夫賈伯斯》能在廣泛發行的首個週末從2,491家劇院收入11萬至12萬美元的票房；然而，在開始廣泛發行的第一天僅開出2,5000美元的成績後，票房預測修改為740萬美元。最終，電影共進帳710萬美元，排名第七<ref name="opening">{{cite web |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |url=http://deadline.com/2015/10/the-last-witch-hunter-paranormal-activity-goosebumps-box-office-preview-1201589142/ |title=Only ''Goosebumps'' Will Prevail In Five-Pic Logjam – Box Office Preview |publisher=[[Deadline.com|Deadline.com]] |date=2015-10-20 |accessdate=2015-11-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdeadline.com%2F2015%2F10%2Fthe-last-witch-hunter-paranormal-activity-goosebumps-box-office-preview-1201589142%2F&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在廣泛發行兩週後的11月10日，環球影業將電影從美國的2,072家劇院中撤出<ref name="usbopulled">{{cite web |url=http://metro.co.uk/2015/11/11/steve-jobs-movie-pulled-from-over-2000-cinemas-in-us-after-flopping-at-box-office-5493699/ |title=Steve Jobs movie pulled from over 2,000 cinemas in US after flopping at box office |first=Caroline |last=Westbrook |work={{link-en|Metro (雜誌)|Metro (magazine)|Metro}} |date=2015-11-11 |accessdate=2015-11-17 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmetro.co.uk%2F2015%2F11%2F11%2Fsteve-jobs-movie-pulled-from-over-2000-cinemas-in-us-after-flopping-at-box-office-5493699%2F&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[綜藝_(雜誌)|綜藝]]》雜誌表示，電影受到票房方面的激烈競爭，以及大眾對賈伯斯以及法斯賓達飾演主角的低調演出感到厭倦的可能性所打擊，而票房表現不佳可能會影響到電影的獲獎機會<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.ftcpublications.com/steve-jobs-box-office-stumble-may-hurt-oscar-chances/ |title=Steve Jobs' box-office stumble may hurt Oscar chances |publisher=FTC Publications Newswire |date=2015-10-26 |accessdate=2015-10-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117022205/http://news.ftcpublications.com/steve-jobs-box-office-stumble-may-hurt-oscar-chances/ |archive-date=2015-11-17 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。在電影於美國廣泛發行後，[[丹尼·鮑伊|丹尼·鮑伊]]對《史帝夫賈伯斯》的票房表現感到失望，同時表示，環球影業將電影的發行弄得「太廣又太急」了，並評論工作室的舉動十分「傲慢」<ref name="boylebo">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-34797483 |title=Danny Boyle 'disappointed' over Steve Jobs US box office flop |publisher=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |date=2015-11-12 |accessdate=2015-11-17 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-34797483&date=2016-09-03 |archive-date=2016-09-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="boylearrogant">{{cite web |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/danny-boyle-says-the-release-strategy-for-steve-jobs-was-arrogant-2015-11?r=UK&IR=T |title=The director of the new movie about Steve Jobs says its release strategy was 'arrogant' |first=James |last=Cook |work=[[商業內幕|Business Insider]] |date=2015-11-29 |accessdate=2015-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151203231403/http://www.businessinsider.com/danny-boyle-says-the-release-strategy-for-steve-jobs-was-arrogant-2015-11?r=UK&IR=T |archive-date=2015-12-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 歷史偏差 ===

[[約翰·史考利|約翰·史考利]]對[[傑夫·丹尼爾|傑夫·丹尼爾]]飾演他的表現讚譽有加，但聲稱該片扭曲了[[蘋果公司|蘋果公司]]在[[Mac系列|Macintosh]]上取得的成功，並認為電影對賈伯斯的詮釋都還比這方面來得好<ref name="sculleymacrumors">{{cite web |url=http://www.macrumors.com/2015/10/06/john-sculley-on-steve-jobs-movie/ |title=John Sculley Talks Steve Jobs Movie, Impressed With Jeff Daniels' Portrayal of Him |last=Sumra |first=Husain |publisher={{link-en|MacRumors|MacRumors}} |date=2015-10-06 |accessdate=2015-11-19 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.macrumors.com%2F2015%2F10%2F06%2Fjohn-sculley-on-steve-jobs-movie%2F&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="sculleywsj">{{cite web |url=http://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2015/10/06/john-sculley-on-steve-jobs-the-movie-the-man-and-his-own-role-in-the-drama/ |title=John Sculley on Steve Jobs: The Movie, the Man and His Own Role in the Drama |last=Chai |first=Barbara |work=[[華爾街日報|The Wall Street Journal]] |date=2015-10-06 |accessdate=2015-11-19 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fblogs.wsj.com%2Fspeakeasy%2F2015%2F10%2F06%2Fjohn-sculley-on-steve-jobs-the-movie-the-man-and-his-own-role-in-the-drama%2F&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="sculleyfrance">{{cite web |url=http://www.france24.com/en/20151105-business-web-summit-dublin-john-sculley-apple-steve-jobs-film |title=Former Apple CEO: 'Steve Jobs was nicer than new film shows' |last=Carroll |first=Stephen |publisher=[[法國24|France 24]] |date=2015-11-05 |accessdate=2015-11-19 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.france24.com%2Fen%2F20151105-business-web-summit-dublin-john-sculley-apple-steve-jobs-film&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[皮克斯動畫工作室|皮克斯動畫工作室]]及[[華特迪士尼動畫工作室|華特迪士尼動畫工作室]]的總裁[[艾德文·卡特姆|艾德文·卡特姆]]認為，賈伯斯看到電影所詮釋的他會「大吃一驚」，覺得自己生前是個比電影中所描繪的他還要更和善的人。卡特姆在接受《[[好萊塢報導|好萊塢報導]]》的記者採訪時表示，「當[賈伯斯]離開蘋果公司時，他步上了經典英雄之旅：他在荒野徘徊，並在NeXT工作，只是那並非工作。他任職於皮克斯動畫工作室，這時，我們失敗了。在這個失敗的過程中，史帝夫得到了一些寶貴的教訓，他改變了，他成了一名善解人意的人，[…]電影錯過了史帝夫的轉變過程」<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-pixars-ed-catmull-good-840292 |title=Disney-Pixar's Ed Catmull on 'Good Dinosaur,' Female Directors and Why Steve Jobs Would Be "Appalled" by 'Steve Jobs' |date=2015-11-20 |last=Belloni |first=Matthew |work=[[好萊塢報導|The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=2015-11-21 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hollywoodreporter.com%2Fnews%2Fdisney-pixars-ed-catmull-good-840292&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2015年8月26日，{{link-en|安德烈·坎寧安|Andrea Cunningham|安迪·坎寧安}}在接受《{{link-en|彭博科技|Bloomberg Technology}}》的記者{{link-en|艾米莉·張 (記者)|Emily Chang (journalist)|艾米莉·張}}的訪問時，稱該片是一部「精彩的電影……這是對一名極其複雜的人物所做的驚人考究。艾倫[·索金]與丹尼·鮑伊塑造出一名非常優秀的賈伯斯」。對於飾演她的{{link-en|莎拉·史努克|Sarah Snook}}，坎寧安表示，儘管她飾演的是個「小角色，但仍然十分敬業地把她演好」<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chang |first1=Emily |title=Andy Cunningham: What It Was Like Working With Steve Jobs |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2015-08-27/andy-cunningham-what-it-was-like-working-with-steve-jobs |website=Bloomberg |accessdate=2015-08-27 |date=2015-08-26 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2015-08-27%2Fandy-cunningham-what-it-was-like-working-with-steve-jobs&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。儘管坎寧安當時沒有與蘋果公司合作，電影仍描繪坎寧安參與了iMac的發表會<ref>{{cite news |last1=Graham |first1=Jefferson |title=She was Steve Jobs' first publicist |url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2015/09/06/she-steve-jobs-first-publicist/71787020/ |accessdate=2015-09-12 |work=USA Today |date=2015-09-06 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Ftech%2F2015%2F09%2F06%2Fshe-steve-jobs-first-publicist%2F71787020%2F&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。記者{{link-en|華特·莫斯伯格|Walt Mossberg}}將《史帝夫賈伯斯》與[[奧森·威爾斯|奧森·威爾斯]]的電影作品《[[大國民|大國民]]》相互比較，後者根據[[威廉·赫茲|威廉·赫茲]]的生平故事改編。莫斯伯格表示，兩者在美學方面皆非常完善，但威爾斯塑造了一組虛構的角色，以澄清他的電影純屬虛構。相較之下，據莫斯伯格（認識賈伯斯達14年）的說法，索金決定使用真實而不是虛構的名字，以免減損電影的質量，也避免使電影成為一部看似是傳記片，但事實並非如此的虛構電影。莫斯伯格表示，「索金電影中描繪的史帝夫·-{}-賈伯斯不是我所認識的那個人。索金挑選並誇大了賈伯斯一些最糟糕的方面，並在他那段年輕且不成熟的職業生涯上大書特書[…]這就像假如你製作了一部名為《[[誰殺了甘迺迪|誰殺了甘迺迪]]》的電影，且將劇情完全-{聚焦}-在甘迺迪的風流及在政壇上的競爭，完全不提民權及[[古巴導彈危機|古巴導彈危機]]。索金選擇結束他的故事，就像賈伯斯準備擺脫一系列前所未有、足以改變世界的產品，蛻變成一名更親切和善的人」<ref name=mossberg>{{cite news |url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/10/21/9578921/steve-jobs-movie-review-walt-mossberg |title=Mossberg: The Steve Jobs I knew isn't in this movie |accessdate=2015-10-22 |last=Mossberg |first=Walt |date=2015-10-21 |work=[[The_Verge|The Verge]] |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2015%2F10%2F21%2F9578921%2Fsteve-jobs-movie-review-walt-mossberg&date=2016-09-04 |archive-date=2016-09-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

